description: Numbers n such that 12^n - 11^n is prime.
comments: Terms greater than 1000 may correspond to unproven strong pseudoprimes.
author: _Mike Oakes_, May 18 2001, May 19 2001
extensions: New term 70067 found by Jean-Louis Charton in 2006 corresponding to a probable prime with 75615 digits. _Jean-Louis Charton_, Sep 02 2009
